Paris Jackson, the daughter of the late Michael Jackson, responded to a tweet that read, “Paris Jackson believes her father, Michael, is innocent of sex abuse claims.” The 20-year-old model and actress responded in a now-deleted tweet, writing, “I actually haven’t made any statements yet, especially regarding how it affects my work life. You guys are reaching a bit. At least this wasn’t a disgusting and attacking article though.” If you don’t know, Leaving Neverland documents the allegations of child molestation against Michael Jackson. Here are the six biggest things we learned from the documentary.